    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.31/2–351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Temporary Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation
                        to the Torquay Conference</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phelps</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Torquay</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-03T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 3, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>396. <gloss target="#t_USTAC1">USTAC</gloss>. Attention Corse. Wilgress phoned
                    Schwenger reporting conversation with Wilson and Holmes pursuant his decision
                    reported <gloss target="#t_ourtel1">ourtel</gloss> 395, February 3. They were
                    “entirely cynical” and unmoved. Stated no results possible Torquay. They would
                    block any progress here. They would also block any <gloss target="#t_OEEC1"
                        >OEEC</gloss> achievement tariff reduction with or without UK. They feel
                    certain European countries will not risk leaving both <gloss target="#t_OEEC1"
                        >OEEC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>, which they consider
                    would be consequence continental intentions. They had no constructive
                    proposal.</p>
                <p>They thought French attitude reported our following telegram further meeting
                    multilaterals entirely insincere.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 396, repeated info London 185, Paris 33 for <gloss
                        target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phelps</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
